From 008b2baff1cb0adff5c2ae5ab03b7d7ccaf9f50b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aneesh Pradhan <apradhan5@horizon.csueastbay.edu>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 17:20:58 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] sepolicy: ensure file_contexts ends with newline

Missing EOF newline made m4 glue the next file's "# Fingerprint HAL"
onto the last context, crashing fc_sort (IndexError on context.split).
---
 sepolicy/vendor/file_contexts | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/sepolicy/vendor/file_contexts b/sepolicy/vendor/file_contexts
index 515099b..628f5e3 100644
--- a/sepolicy/vendor/file_contexts
+++ b/sepolicy/vendor/file_contexts
@@ -2,4 +2,4 @@
 /dev/esfp0                                               u:object_r:fingerprint_device:s0
 /sys/devices/soc/0.et320/etspi_enable                    u:object_r:sysfs_devices_fingerprint:s0
 /sys/devices/platform/egis_input(/.*)?                   u:object_r:sysfs_devices_fingerprint:s0
-/(vendor|system/vendor)/bin/hw/android\.hardware\.biometrics\.fingerprint@2\.1-service-ets u:object_r:hal_fingerprint_default_exec:s0
\ No newline at end of file
+/(vendor|system/vendor)/bin/hw/android\.hardware\.biometrics\.fingerprint@2\.1-service-ets u:object_r:hal_fingerprint_default_exec:s0
-- 
2.53.0

